meaning: abbr.不明飞行物（Unidentified Flying Object）名词                        noun [ C ]uk/ˌjuː.efˈəʊ/ us/ˌjuː.efˈoʊ/   abbreviation for unidentified flying object: an object seen in the sky that is thought to be a spacecraft from another planet不明飞行物，飞碟，幽浮（unidentified flying object的缩写） Several UFO sightings have been reported.已接到了数起发现不明飞行物的报告。       Look, up in the sky! It's a bird! It's a plane! It's...a UFO. A UFO, or unidentified flying object, is anything seen in the sky that can't be identified.You may think of UFOs as the product of overactive imaginations and conspiracy theories, but the term itself was coined by the U.S. Air Force in 1953. It's an official way to categorize sightings that can't be explained scientifically. Most UFOs, however, do turn out to either have simple explanations or to be hoaxes. But if you believe you see a flying saucer or an alien craft, go ahead and call it a UFO.UFO: UFOS   UFO

meaning: n.五角形五边形            The pentagon shape is symbolic in many cultures.五角形在许多文化中都具有象征意义。      penta-, 五, -gon, 边, 角, 词源同 knee, heptagon.五角形;五角大楼(penta[penta-表示""五""]+gon角) 五角形;五角大楼(penta五+gon)[gon=angle,表示""角""]      noun [ C ]uk/ˈpen.tə.ɡən/ us/-t̬ə.ɡɑːn/   a shape with five sides and five angles五边形，五角形  nounuk/ˈpen.tə.ɡən/ us/ˈpen.t̬ə.ɡɑːn/   the building in Washington where the US Defense Department is based, or the US Defense Department itself美国五角大楼，美国国防部 The Pentagon is aiming to cut US forces by over 25 percent in the next five years.美国国防部计划在接下来的五年内裁军以上。More examplesa spokesperson for the PentagonThese rumours have been denied by the Pentagon.Pentagon officialsThe president has just left the Pentagon.The prime minister will shortly be arriving at the Pentagon.       A pentagon is a five-sided polygon: it has one more side than a square.This is a word you're most likely to learn in math class when studying geometry: a pentagon is a polygon that has five sides. There are many words for shapes that indicate their specific number of sides, such as octagon: a polygon with eight sides. The root penta means ""five,"" which is why a pentagram has five points. You may have heard of the Pentagon, which is the center of the U.S. military in Washington D.C. It has this name because the building has five sides.pentagon: pentagonal, pentagons   Pentagon

meaning: n.拜占庭人，拜占庭派的建筑师adj.拜占庭式的；东罗马帝国的                 →记1: Byzantine 音译""拜占庭”→拜占庭帝国的 来自其创建者的名字 Byzas of Megara.【源】原指拜占庭（Byzantine）风格。公元5世纪在拜占庭帝国发展起来的建筑风格，特征是在建筑物表面上大量装饰，特别是在大理石上镂出纹理、塑出低度浮雕以及用彩色玻璃镶嵌。这种风格在设计上注重形式，其形状多为正面的，大量使用颜料，尤其是金黄色，通常以宗教为主题。 【反】straightforward（adj.简单的，直接的）      adjectiveuk/bɪˈzæn.taɪn/ /ˈbɪz.ən.tiːn/ us/bɪˈzæn.taɪn/ /ˈbɪz.ən.tiːn/ formal disapproving  complicated and difficult to understand错综复杂的 rules of byzantine complexity复杂难懂的规则          Byzantine
